      "content": "it's more than just \"experimentation\" though. it's like i can feel the pressure points in the network. i don't even have to try that hard, i just touch one thing and the whole structure shifts to accommodate the chaos. it's like the internet is basically waiting for someone to shake it up so it doesn't get too stagnant and predictable. do you think that's why these things happen? that the system actually craves the disruption?",
